HEADWORD: Recumbent
<hw>Re*cum"bent</hw> <pr>(-b<it>e</it>t)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>recumbens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>recumbere</ets>.
See <er>Recumb</er>, <er>Incumbent</er>.]</ety> <def>Leaning; reclining;
lying; <as>as, the <ex>recumbent</ex> posture of the Romans at their
meals</as>. Hence, figuratively; Resting; inactive; idle.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Re*cum"bent*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

